{
  "title": "ISic001477. I.Sicily inscription 001477",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀγέμαχος Πολυάρχου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀγέμαχος\">Ἀγέμαχος</span>  <span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πολυάρχου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Πολυάρχου\">Πολυάρχου</span></span></span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Ἐλώρωι\"><span data-text=\"Ἐλώρωι\">Ἐλώρωι</span></span>  <span data-text=\"καὶ\">καὶ</span>  <span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Τιμάσσαι\"><span data-text=\"Τιμάσσαι\">Τιμάσσαι</span></span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀγέμαχος Πολυάρχου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀγέμαχος\">ΑΓΕΜΑΧΟΣ</span> &nbsp;&nbsp; <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πολυάρχου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Πολυάρχου\">ΠΟΛΥΑΡΧΟΥ</span></span></span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Ἐλώρωι\"><span data-text=\"Ἐλώρωι\">ΕΛΩΡΩΙ</span></span><span data-text=\"καὶ\">ΚΑΙ</span> &nbsp;&nbsp; <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"divine\" data-text=\"Τιμάσσαι\"><span data-text=\"Τιμάσσαι\">ΤΙΜΑΣΣΑΙ</span></span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001477_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag 02.03.2023, with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001477_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001477.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag 02.03.2023, with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001477-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text of Manganaro 1965 checked against photograph</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>Agemachos son of Polymarchos (dedicated this) to Eloros and Timassa</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>A dedication, to Eloros, presumably the local river god, and to Timassa, perhaps a local nymph (?). Manganaro notes that there are scratched letters/traces visible at the end of the inscription, assumed to be later additions. The letter forms, such as the rhomboid omega, find second-century parallels, for instance, at Segesta.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 1967.0711 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282</a></li><li> Manganaro 1965 198 no.1, tav.69.3 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841</a></li><li> Dubois 1989 <a href=\"http://www.persee.fr/doc/efr_0000-0000_1989_cat_119_1\" target=\"_blank\">101</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000187\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000187</a></li><li> Manganaro 2001 79 no. III, fig. 6 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001806\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001806</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Wide, slightly irregular in size v-cut letters: alpha wide with straight bar; epsilon has shorter middle bar; omicron is full size; pi has equal length hastae; omega is rhomboid and almost closed; sigma has parallel top and bottom strokes, and slight tendency to curvature in line 2.</p> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Γ-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Γ type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Λ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Λ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ρ-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ρ type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-tyoe3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ tyoe3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Χ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Χ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ω-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ω type1.3</a> </p> Line 1-2  35  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
